  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "/qsrCHD/82r7HhbuuWmqPiCj+AA=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:31.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "When Connect runs the native SyncManager against a Switchboard AND the Swarm plugin at the same time, every operation is stored in three places:\n\n```\nCONNECT (browser)          SWITCHBOARD (server)       SWARM NETWORK\nPGlite                     PostgreSQL                  /bytes + feeds\n  - operations ----------> - operations\n              <----------\n                                                       - operation batches\n  - operations ----------------------------------------> - manifests\n```\n\n**Storage cost**: 3x per operation (PGlite + PostgreSQL + Swarm).\n\n**The upside is optional resilience**:\n- Can recover from either Switchboard OR Swarm\n- Team collaboration continues working via Switchboard\n- Censorship-resistant backup via Swarm\n- Useful during migration or for high-value data\n\n**The cost is real**:\n- Triple bandwidth for writes\n- Triple stamp/storage cost for operations on Swarm\n- Two sync paths to reason about for conflicts\n\nThis is Architecture C \u2014 not a target state but a useful interim for users who want both properties simultaneously, or while migrating off a Switchboard.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:31.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:31.000Z"
    }
  },
